# Meeting lifecycle — approve + notify lock

Authoritative contract: `docs/platforms/backend/contracts/meeting-domain.md` §9. Website: `docs/platforms/website/flow-customer-meetings.md` §6.

## Ability (Customer)

- `MEETING` subs: `create` | `read` | `update` | `delete` | `approve` with optional `meeting` target.
- `update` (and child writes): require `notify_status === NOT_STARTED`.
- `delete`: `DRAFT` + `NOT_STARTED` only.
- `approve`: `DRAFT` + `NOT_STARTED` + quorum + ≥1 agenda + ≥1 PRE_START decision + template mode rules.
- Meeting stays non-actor. GQL extras on `_Meeting` only (not on unbounded list).

## Template mode

Use `resolveMeetingNotifyTemplateMode` (backend helper). Do not invent a second approve engine on the website — callout may mirror the helper; Ability enforces.

WhatsApp slot types: `ADWHATS` | `ADWHATS_PRO`. Email slot: `EJTMAA_EMAIL` | `CUSTOM_EMAIL`.

## Forbidden

- Approving without Ability completeness.
- Mutating meeting content after notify leaves `NOT_STARTED`.
- Starting notify pipeline inside `approve`.
- Attaching `canApprove` to root-many `meetings` list.
